olimits _{n}(\mathbb {F})=\mathop {\mathrm {Mat}}
olimits _{n}(\mathbb {F})^{	imes } the group of invertible elements of \mathop {\mathrm {Mat}}
olimits _{n}(\mathbb {F}) under matrix multiplication.

Let R be Equivalence relation on a set X. Then we define the Quotient set
X/R := \{[a]\mid  a\in  X\}
is the set of equivalence classes. We have a natural surjective map X\to  X/R sending a\mapsto [a].
